<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="1695" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1695">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 817.812/80.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Chargé d’Affaires of Salvador</gloss>.</hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-16">
                                    <hi rend="italic">July 16, 1914</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to acknowledge receipt of your
                            communication of July 8, and to say that your Government has been
                            misinformed in respect to the proposed treaty with Nicaragua. The
                            negotiations have not been concluded and no treaty has been presented to
                            the Senate for ratification. The Department is conferring, in
                            confidence, with the Foreign Relations Committee of the Senate in regard
                            to a tentative draft, the terms of which have not been made public. If
                            the matter in which your Government has expressed an interest, becomes a
                            matter for practical consideration, we shall be pleased to examine into
                            the protest which you present.</p>
                        <p>With assurances [etc.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>